@icing 
[libcurl.log](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/16396694/libcurl.log)

The sockets `23, 49, 50, 265, 281` were spuriously passed to the socket callback at `20:45:15`

@JulesRapanga  and others: I propose #14296 as the "real" fix for this issue. It would be great if you could verify this. Thanks!

Note: this will no longer produce the debug output as in the previous PR. I guess we need to add some `CURLMOPT_DEBUGFUNCTION` in the future to add tracing to this.

Also, in addition, this PR will make connection shutdown timeouts happen. So, in case a server is slow responding, you should see the sockets for shutdowns be removed after lastest 2 seconds.
